She
was
still
looking
at
him
with
the
most
speaking
amazement.
"You
like
it,
my
Emma,
as
little
as
I
feared.
I
wish
our
opinions
were
the
same.
But
in
time
they
will.
Time,
you
may
be
sure,
will
make
one
or
the
other
of
us
think
differently;
and,
in
the
meanwhile,
we
need
not
talk
much
on
the
subject."
"You
mistake
me,
you
quite
mistake
me,"
she
replied,
exerting
herself.
"It
is
not
that
such
a
circumstance
would
now
make
me
unhappy,
